The cook who had forgotten to gut the pig had not yet faded from my recollection. So I began looking all round the dining-room, in case any clockwork toy should jump out of the wall, especially after they had begun to beat a servant for dressing the bruise on his master’s arm with white wool instead of purple. And my suspicions were not far out. Instead of punish- ment there came Trimalchio’s decree that he should be made a free man, for sear anyone might be able to say that our hero had been wounded by a slave.
